On June 23, 2009, the White House held a roundtable discussion on Title IX, the legislation that bans sex discrimination in schools. The event, which marked the 37th anniversary of Title IX, featured White House Senior Advisor Valerie Jarrett, Education Secretary Arne Duncan, and various women athletes and scientists. The roundtable was streamed live on the web and included an online chat for viewers to participate in. The event aimed to honor the work of Title IX advocates and demonstrate the Obama Administration's commitment to the legislation. Participants included Billie Jean King, Dominique Dawes, and other notable figures in sports and education.